<subSubSection id="1BD8652DFFF0FFEEE30602E9FB83FCD7" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="537D36A6FFF0FFEEE30602E9FB83FCD7" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,2013]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">
[TL: 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFF0FFEEE34C02E8FD70FD0F" box="[630,723,690,716]" name="Ukraine" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
, Kiverce, Podalia], 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF0FFEEE29702E9FBDEFD0E" author="Varga, Z. &amp; Szabo, S. &amp; Kozma, P." box="[941,1149,690,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" pagination="65 - 68" refId="ref11796" refString="Varga, Z., Szabo, S. &amp; Kozma, P. (2005) Melitaea ogygia kovacsi Varga 1967 (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae) in the Pannonian region: taxonomy, bionomy, conservation biology. In: Kuhn, E., Feldmann, R., Thomas, J. &amp; Settele, J. (Eds.), Studies on the Ecology and Conservation of Butterflies in Europe, 1: general concepts and case studies, pp. 65 - 68. [Conference Proceedings, UFZ Leipzig - Halle, December 2005]" type="proceedings paper" year="2005">
Varga 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF0FFEEE2CE02E9FB86FD0F" box="[1012,1061,690,716]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">et al</emphasis>
. (2005)
</bibRefCitation>
placed this taxon with 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF0FFEEE44402E9FE0FFD33" authority="Fruhstorfer, 1908" authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ogygia">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF0FFEEE44402E9FF40FD33" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">M. ogygia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF0FFEEE1D0028CFE0FFD33" author="Fruhstorfer, H." box="[234,428,726,752]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" pagination="310" refId="ref9058" refString="Fruhstorfer, H. (1908) Neue Argynnis und Melitaea. Internationale Entomologische Zeitschrift, 1, 310." type="journal article" year="1908">Fruhstorfer, 1908</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
following which 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF0FFEEE34A028CFC97FD33" author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, K. &amp; Vegvari, Z. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[624,820,726,753]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" pagination="245 - 255" refId="ref11470" refString="Toth, J. P., Varga, K., Vegvari, Z. &amp; Varga, Z. (2013) Distribution of the eastern knapweed fritillary (Melitaea ornata Christoph, 1893) (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae): past, present and future. Journal of Insect Conservation, 17, 245 - 255. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10841 - 012 - 9503 - 2" type="journal article" year="2013">
Tóth 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF0FFEEE391028DFD7FFD33" box="[683,732,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">et al</emphasis>
. (2013)
</bibRefCitation>
placed it with 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF0FFEEE2E2028DFBEBFD33" box="[984,1096,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF0FFEEE2E2028DFBEBFD33" box="[984,1096,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF0FFEEE56F028CFA34FD32" author="Russell, PJ &amp; Tennent, W. J." box="[1109,1431,726,753]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" pagination="27 - 56" refId="ref10922" refString="Russell, PJ. C. &amp; Tennent, W. J. (2016) A synonymic list of names associated with western Palaearctic Melitaea phoebe (Denis &amp; Schiffermuller, 1775) species group taxa M. phoebe; M. punica Oberthur, 1876; M. ornata Christoph, 1893) (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae). Nota Lepidopterologica, 39 (1), 27 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / nl. 39.5929" type="journal article" year="2016">Russell &amp; Tennent (2016: 45</bibRefCitation>
, note 21) were in agreement with the latter association, as are the present authors.
</paragraph>
